Description:
Another 6x1km interval run. Tried to maintain a sub 5 pace per km and was holding strong until last two efforts. Something wasn’t sitting right in my stomach and had to fight off feeling like vomit but still held onto a 5:20/kn in that km average. 

Next week is fartlek so will be interesting to see that play out

5km tempo run in a new location. Legs and heart were feeling good the whole run, little loopy to keep up with Hassan but a solid 5km effort for the week. Felt really good with the fast pace moments and bringing in that striding
6km easy run easiest feeling best run I’ve ever done

Was supposed to be a full 12km run but running in 30 degree heat was near impossible. What should have felt like an easy normal pace quickly ran my heart rate up due to the heat so had to take lots of breaks and walking minutes to keep heart rate lower. 

Lesson learnt don’t run when it’s fucking hot

6x1km at sub 5-5:15 pace. Walking break between km.

First run where I discovered how to stride better with more glute drive for a more open gate. Massive improvement made the fast pace feel way slower than it really was. Once I get better at maintaining that I should be able to hold a sub 5km pace for way longer than I can now

Day 2 of the training plan had me set for a tempo 5km at threshold pace. Goal was not to set a new PB but opening up that first km with a massive 4:20/km split had me feeling good. Tried to push hard early to make the most of the tempo duration and ended up with the new sub 26 minute PB. Hoping to crush this again with the next tempo next week. Might train somewhere else
Starting off the first run of the new half marathon training plan. Day 1 6km easy run no pace goal just need to lock onto zone 2 and hold
5km easy run pace with one hard push for the last km for fun

Left the watch at work so no idea if I kept the zone 2 goal but nonetheless solid effort

Week 1 of the new run plan starting Monday so preparing myself

Goal was to hit sub 1hr. 

Paced out first 2km for a 6-6:30/km
Then aimed to avg 5:45 for kms 3-8
Then smash sub 5:30 for last 2km

Absolutely killed it. 
Sub 55:00 coming next
Nice easy 5km without pushing any pace or excessive heart rate.
Smashed out a solid 5km speed run. Forgot the watch so mainly ran on feeling.

Slightly underprepared for the run with not the most hydration and fueling up to the run. Decided to take a different approach to the speed training and work on building the lactate threshold. 

Pushed as hard and fast as I could and held for as long as I could. Took a couple of breaks when the heart rate maxed out as well as building a huge stitch on the right side of my chest. Gotta work on my breathing on the next run to prevent that. 5km pb attempt for a sub 26 next week. Based off the splits I should be going for a 25:45 ish

Recovery run to get the body moving again after recovering from the 18.5km long run recently. 

Sun was too hot to push harder for longer so might need to start night running or waking up early. Yuck

Pushed as hard as I could for as long as I could. 

6:30 pace wasn’t as sustainable as I had hoped but will continue trying. 
 
Definitely needed a better pacing strategy with proper fuelling and hydration but super proud of this effort.

Half marathon maybe a month out!!

Original goal was to start slower and negative split, but my legs didn’t agree with that idea.

Lowkey mad I didn’t get the sub 26 but it’s coming

1km conversational pace, 400m sub 5 pace, 400m conversational x 2 then rest for a 3 minutes. Repeat Hassan Alsharia

You thought I was done with the 5km earlier today? Don’t tell my legs I just ran 12km today they haven’t found out yet
New place same legs
Nice easy 2.5km split, stopped to eat some tacos, then smashed out the second half. Building up the endurance level with an easy run

Pushed hard on this one to set a new PB

Sub 27 coming soon
